
Problem Statement
Build a City Research Assistant that helps users compare two cities before relocating.
The user can ask questions such as:
“Should I move to Pune or Bengaluru?”
The application collects information from multiple sources:
•	OpenStreetMap / Nominatim for hospitals, schools, public transport, parks, and nearby amenities. 
•	Open-Meteo for current weather and forecast comparison. 
•	Tavily API for job opportunities, cost of living, traffic, lifestyle, and recent city-related information. 
•	Open Library API for books related to the cities, local culture, travel, and relocation. 
Multiple specialized agents perform these research tasks in parallel. A final comparison agent combines the results and generates a clear recommendation based on the user’s priorities.
The application will use Streamlit for the user interface, Smolagents for agent orchestration, and the OpenAI API for reasoning, summarization, and recommendation generation.
 








