Agents
1. Coordinator Agent
The Coordinator Agent receives the user’s question and extracts:
•	Cities to compare 
•	User priorities 
•	Profession or job preference 
•	Climate preference 
•	Family requirements 
•	Budget expectations 
It then assigns tasks to the specialized agents.
2. Amenities Agent
Uses OpenStreetMap and Nominatim to compare:
•	Hospitals 
•	Schools and colleges 
•	Bus stops and railway stations 
•	Parks 
•	Restaurants 
•	Supermarkets 
•	Coworking spaces 
•	Other nearby facilities 
3. Weather Agent
Uses Open-Meteo to compare:
•	Current temperature 
•	Minimum and maximum temperature 
•	Rainfall 
•	Humidity 
•	Wind speed 
•	Forecast conditions 
4. Web Research Agent
Uses the Tavily API to research:
•	Cost of living 
•	Rental prices 
•	Job market 
•	Major industries 
•	Average commute 
•	Traffic conditions 
•	Safety and lifestyle 
•	Recent developments 
5. Book Recommendation Agent
Uses the Open Library API to recommend books related to:
•	Local history 
•	Regional culture 
•	Travel 
•	Language 
•	Relocation 
•	Professional development 
6. Comparison Agent
The Comparison Agent receives the outputs from all agents and creates:
•	Side-by-side city comparison 
•	Advantages and disadvantages 
•	Category-wise scores 
•	Recommendation based on user priorities 
•	Important limitations or missing data 
 
Suggested Smolagents Design
ManagerAgent
├── AmenitiesTool
├── WeatherTool
├── TavilyResearchTool
├── OpenLibraryTool
└── CityComparisonAgent
The API tools should return structured Python dictionaries. The OpenAI-powered comparison agent should explain the results but should not invent unavailable numerical values.
The Streamlit interface should display:
•	Chat-style user input 
•	Selected cities 
•	Agent execution status 
•	API/tool calls 
•	Weather comparison 
•	Amenity counts 
•	Research findings 
•	Recommended books 
•	Final relocation recommendation 
The OpenAI API key should be loaded securely from a .env file:
OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key
TAVILY_API_KEY=your_tavily_api_key

